Privacy Policy for Wealthview

Effective Date: 7th October, 2025
Last Updated: 24th January, 2026

Wealthview (“We,” “Our,” or “Us”) respects your privacy and is committed to protecting it through this Privacy Policy. This Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you access or use the Wealthview application (“App”) built on the Pi Network platform, including via the Pi Browser and Pi SDK.

By using Wealthview, you agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.

1. Scope of This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy applies solely to Wealthview and does not govern data handled directly by Pi Network, Pi Browser, or Pi Wallet. Pi Network operates under its own Privacy Policy, which you are encouraged to review separately.

2. Information We Collect
2.1 Information Provided via Pi Network

When you log in using Pi Network authentication, we may receive limited information authorized by Pi Network, such as:

Pi username

Pi user ID

Public profile information permitted by Pi Network

We do not collect passwords, private keys, passphrases, or wallet credentials.

2.2 User-Provided Information

You may voluntarily provide additional information when using Wealthview features, such as:

Preferences or settings

Feedback, messages, or support requests

Optional profile data (if applicable)

2.3 Automatically Collected Information

We may collect limited technical data to improve app performance, including:

Device type and operating system

App usage statistics

Error logs and performance metrics

This data is anonymized or pseudonymized where possible.

3. How We Use Your Information

We use collected information to:

Provide and maintain Wealthview services

Enable Pi Network–based authentication

Improve functionality, analytics, and user experience

Respond to inquiries and provide support

Ensure compliance with applicable laws and platform rules

Prevent fraud, abuse, or misuse of the App

We do not sell or rent your personal data.

4. Pi Wallet and Financial Transactions

Wealthview does not:

Store Pi wallet private keys

Access wallet credentials

Execute transactions without explicit user approval

All Pi transactions occur through the Pi Wallet, governed entirely by Pi Network’s infrastructure and security protocols.

5. Data Sharing and Disclosure

We may share limited data only in the following circumstances:

With Pi Network, as required for authentication and platform compliance

With service providers performing app-related services under confidentiality obligations

To comply with legal requirements, lawful requests, or regulatory obligations

To protect rights and security, including prevention of fraud or abuse

We do not share data for advertising or profiling purposes.

6. Data Retention

We retain personal information only for as long as necessary to:

Fulfill the purposes outlined in this Policy

Comply with legal, accounting, or regulatory obligations

When no longer required, data is securely deleted or anonymized.

7. Data Security

We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational safeguards to protect your information. However, no digital platform can guarantee absolute security, and use of the App is at your own risk.

8. User Rights and Choices

Depending on applicable law, you may have the right to:

Access the data we hold about you

Request correction or deletion of your data

Withdraw consent where processing is consent-based

Requests may be submitted via the contact details below.

9. Children’s Privacy

Wealthview is not intended for children under the age of 13 (or the minimum age required by local law). We do not knowingly collect personal data from children.

10. Third-Party Links and Services

The App may contain links to third-party platforms or services. We are not responsible for their privacy practices or content. Use of such services is at your own discretion.

11. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy at any time. Changes will be effective upon posting within the App or Pi Browser interface. Continued use of Wealthview constitutes acceptance of the revised Policy.

12. Contact Us

If you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

Wealthview Support
Email: henryuzuwe@gmail.com
Platform: Pi Network / Pi Browser
